
Compiling the Typelib

 - Use Gecko SDK from: http://developer.mozilla.org/en/docs/Gecko_SDK
 - If you are using windows you can download the additional required DLL files from:
 		- http://www.driverskit.net/
 		- http://www.mozdev.org/notes/hello_world_js_component_win.html

 - SDK for Intel Mac:
 		- http://www.oxymoronical.com/view/1114
 		- http://developer.mozilla.org/en/docs/Mac_OS_X_Build_Prerequisites
 		- http://developer.mozilla.org/en/docs/XPIDL:xpidl
 			- Install libIDL with FINK
 					# apt-get update
 					# apt-get install orbit orbit-dev glib
 			- Download mozilla source (ftp://ftp.mozilla.org/pub/mozilla.org/mozilla/releases/)
 			- Install GTK
 					# apt-get install gtk+
 					# sudo apt-get install libidl2
 			- Configure mozilla source:
 					- Add .mozconfig file to source root
 							mk_add_options MOZ_CO_PROJECT=browser
							ac_add_options --enable-application=browser
 					# ./configure
 					# make -C config
					# make -C nsprpub
					# make -C xpcom/typelib
 			- Lots of errors but it works! The xpidl shouldnow be in dist/bin/
 		
 		
 - {sdk_dir}/bin/xpidl -m typelib -w -v -I {sdk_dir}/idl -e nsIFirePHP.xpt nsIFirePHP.idl
 

To recompile the IDL file:
	- Use the compiled xpidl appjust compiled and link against the idl files from http://www.oxymoronical.com/view/1114
	- Very ugly but no time to get this cleaned up now at the moment.

	# cd /pinf/packages/com.googlecode.firephp/FirefoxExtension/components
	# /Users/cadorn/Downloads/MacOSX-OpenSource/mozilla/dist/bin/xpidl -m typelib -w -v -I "/Users/cadorn/Downloads/MacOSX-OpenSource/gecko-sdk-mac-intel-1.8.1.3 Folder/idl" -e nsIFirePHP.xpt nsIFirePHP.idl
	
	
	